main event: A person in Jeffersonville, Ohio observed an unidentified object in the sky on August 1, 1966 at around 9:15 PM.
interesting points: The object was initially seen as a beam of light in the sky, then transformed into three red lights arranged in a triangle.
The object was observed for around 3 minutes.
The witness could not precisely estimate the speed or distance of the object, but described it as 'pretty fast' and estimated it to be 2-3 miles away.
The object was observed outdoors, away from the city, while the witness was not moving.
The witness stated the object appeared solid and did not give off any sound.
sighted object: three red lights in a triangular formation
